There was just one away win on matchday 3 in the Nigeria Professional Football League (NPFL) as Lobi Stars beat Shooting 2-1 in Makurdi. TheCable examines how the 16 NPFL teams fared across various stadiums. Akwa United 1-0 Gombe Friday Ubong’s 81st minute spot kick was the difference between Akwa United and Gombe at the Godswill Akpabio Stadium in Uyo. Enyimba FC 0-1 Rivers United Enyimba suffered their first home defeat in the hands of Rivers United in front of their home crowd in Aba. Heartland FC 1-0 Dakkada Heartland pipped Dakkada to earn all three points in Owerri. Kwara United 1-0 Wikki Tourists Ebuka Anekwe’s 53rd minute own goal was the difference between Kwara United and Wikki Tourists in Ilorin. Lobi Stars 2-1 3SC Lobi Stars came from behind to beat Shooting Stars of Ibadan in Makurdi, Benue state capital. MFM FC 1-0 Plateau Precious Roland header in the 55th of play was all the Olukoya boys needed to win their first match of the campaign against Plateau United. Remo Stars 0-0 Nasarawa United It was a goalless affair between Reno Stars and Nasarawa United in Ijebu. Sunshine Stars 0-0 Enugu Rangers Sunshine Stars and Enugu Rangers also settled for a goalless draw at the Adamasingba Stadium in Ibadan. *On Thursday, Niger Tornadoes will take on Abia Warriors while Katsina United have Kano Pillars to contend with.